sub_title: Assistant Legal Officer at the International Criminal Court. Public International Law practitioner. Colombian attorney.
summary:
Rafael Andres is a Colombian Lawyer (LLB – Universidad Externado de Colombia, 2017) with further studies in France (LLM Human Rights Security and Development – Lille Catholic University, France, 2018). 

Rafael holds solid and varied experience in both the private sector (1493 Attorneys, Bogota, Colombia), the public sector in Colombia (Colombian Ministry of Foreign Affairs and National Historical Memory Center), NGO's (ADC-ICT and IBA in the Hague, Netherlands), International Organizations (ICC) and research Institutions (SAIFAC, in Johannesburg, South Africa). He has also been a volunteer and activist at Amnesty International in Johannesburg, South Africa and The Hague, Netherlands.
